dct_description_sm: Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Contour interval 20 feet. Shows limestone locations in a portion of Monroe County and small portions of Owen and Greene counties in Indiana. "39th Annual report Indiana Department of Geology." Base map: Bloomington Quadrangle Indiana : Topography/U.S.G.S. 1909. "J.W. Beede, in charge of field work."    Detached from: Geology of the Bloomington quadrangle / J. W. Beede. In Thirty-ninth annual report of Department of Geology and Natural Resources, Indiana, 1914. Indianapolis: Wm. B. Burford, 1915. Page 191.
Imprint: [Indianapolis] : Indiana Dept. of Geology [and Natural Resources], [1915]; Imprint: [Indianapolis] : [Wm. B. Burford], [1915]
